headline: Tractor Supply Raises More Than $1 Million to Support FFA Students in Pursuing Postsecondary Studies
summary: BRENTWOOD, Tenn., September 04, 2025--Tractor Supply Company (NASDAQ: TSCO), the largest rural lifestyle retailer in the United States, announced today it has raised $1 million for the Tractor Supply 2026 FFA Future Leaders Scholarship fund. The fund supports scholarships for FFA students pursuing studies in the skilled trades and agriculture-related majors. Since its inception, the annual fundraiser has generated a total of more than $4 million over four years.

headline: Dollar Tree's Treasure Hunt Meets Tariff Trouble
summary: Dollar Tree posted strong Q2 comps and traffic gains, but tariff risks and flat EPS outlook limit near-term upside near $100. Read why DLTR stock is a hold.
